    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Remove and install engine mount torque rod"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Front under cover removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000850",
          "label": "Front under cover removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Torque rod removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "359_3.0_jpn_11034050_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Place a plate on the transmission and support it with a transmission jack, and remove the torque rod (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not loosen the torque rod mounting bolt (B)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Torque Rod Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "359_3.0_jpn_11034051_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the torque rod and tighten the new mounting nut (A). When installing the bolt on the front sub-frame side, align the non-turn plate (B) of the bolt with the notch (C) in the guide section of the front sub-frame, insert the bolt, and install the nut."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front Under Cover Installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000850",
          "label": "Front Under Cover Installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
